{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a044", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 68, "line_end": 68, "verbatim": "**Row 1:** Subject 001 was randomized to drug A. At the end of the double-blind treatment epoch, they were assigned to open label A; thus, their ARMCD is \"AA\". They received the treatment to which they were assigned, so ACTRMCD is also \"AA\".", "parent_section": "§DM.3 [Example 3]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a045", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 70, "line_end": 70, "verbatim": "**Row 2:** Subject 002 was randomized to drug A. They were lost to follow-up during the double-blind treatment epoch, so never reached the open label epoch, when they would have been assigned to either drug A or the rescue element. Their ARMCD is \"A\". This case illustrates the exception to the rule that ARMCD, ARM, ACTARMCD, and ACTARM must be populated with values from the TA dataset.", "parent_section": "§DM.3 [Example 3]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a046", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 72, "line_end": 72, "verbatim": "**Row 3:** Subject \"003\" was randomized to drug A, but received drug B. At the end of the double-blind treatment epoch, they were assigned to rescue treatment. ARMCD shows the result of their assignments, \"AR\"; ACTARMCD shows their actual treatment, \"BR\".", "parent_section": "§DM.3 [Example 3]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
