{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a094", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 179, "line_end": 179, "verbatim": "| CRACE01-CRACE04 | 10 | (same) | Race | Select each value that applies if the subject answered \"AMERICAN INDIAN OR ALASKA NATIVE\". Check all that apply. | Text | SUPPDM.QVAL | For each value that applies, SUPPDM.QVAL where SUPPDM.QNAM =\"CRACEn\" and SUPPDM.QLABEL = \"Collected Race n\" where n is the choice value. | (RACEC) | ALASKA NATIVE; AMERICAN INDIAN; CARIBBEAN INDIAN; CENTRAL AMERICAN INDIAN | | | checkbox | |", "parent_section": "§DM.4 [Example 4]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a095", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 180, "line_end": 180, "verbatim": "| CRACE05-CRACE10 | 11 | (same) | Race | Select each value that applies if the subject answered \"ASIAN\". Check all that apply. | Text | SUPPDM.QVAL | For each value that applies, SUPPDM.QVAL where SUPPDM.QNAM =\"CRACEn\" and SUPPDM.QLABEL = \"Collected Race n\" where n is the choice value. | (RACEC) | ASIAN AMERICAN; ASIAN INDIAN; BANGLADESHI; CHINESE; JAPANESE; KOREAN | | | checkbox | CRACE05-CRACE10 |", "parent_section": "§DM.4 [Example 4]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a096", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 181, "line_end": 181, "verbatim": "| CRACE11-CRACE17 | 12 | (same) | Race | Select each value that applies if the subject answered \"BLACK OR AFRICAN AMERICAN\". Check all that apply. | Text | SUPPDM.QVAL | For each value that applies, SUPPDM.QVAL where SUPPDM.QNAM =\"CRACEn\" and SUPPDM.QLABEL = \"Collected Race n\" where n is the choice value. | (RACEC) | AFRICAN; AFRICAN AMERICAN; AFRICAN CARIBBEAN; BAHAMIAN; BARBADIAN; BLACK; BLACK CENTRAL AMERICAN | | | checkbox | |", "parent_section": "§DM.4 [Example 4]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a097", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 182, "line_end": 182, "verbatim": "| CRACE18-CRACE21 | 13 | (same) | Race | Select each value that applies if the subject answered \"WHITE\". Check all that apply. | Text | SUPPDM.QVAL | For each value that applies, SUPPDM.QVAL where SUPPDM.QNAM =\"CRACEn\" and SUPPDM.QLABEL = \"Collected Race n\" where n is the choice value. | (RACEC) | ARAB; EUROPEAN; MIDDLE EASTERN; RUSSIAN | | | checkbox | |", "parent_section": "§DM.4 [Example 4]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a098", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 184, "line_end": 184, "verbatim": "The value of RACE is used to represent the high-level racial designation as a single collected value per CDISC Controlled Terminology in dm.xpt. When more than 1 choice is selected, the value is represented with \"MULTIPLE\" as shown in this example. **Note:** Only those variables relevant to this example are shown.", "parent_section": "§DM.4 [Example 4]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a099", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 186, "line_end": 186, "verbatim": "**Row 1:** Shows that USUBJID ABC789-010-045 designated 1 race, \"WHITE\", as the value that best describes their race.", "parent_section": "§DM.4 [Example 4]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a100", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 188, "line_end": 188, "verbatim": "**Row 2:** Shows that USUBJID ABC789-010-046 designated 1 race, \"ASIAN\", as the value that best describes their race.", "parent_section": "§DM.4 [Example 4]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "md_dmDM_ex_a101", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "file": "knowledge_base/domains/DM/examples.md", "line_start": 190, "line_end": 190, "verbatim": "**Row 3:** Shows that USUBJID ABC789-010-047 designated multiple races as the values that best describe their race. \"MULTIPLE\" is assigned in RACE.", "parent_section": "§DM.4 [Example 4]", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "general-purpose", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_md_v1.9.1", "ts": "2026-05-06T03:30:00Z"}}
